      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is a lot of work for something that’s inlined here and not independently tested. I don’t necessarily have a problem with the approach, but I think that it’s just hefty to have this be in the implementation of this method, you know?\n\nBut I also think that the type_traits thing I suggested yesterday would be less code (and more easily understood/reviewed).\n\n  AssignIfInRange(value,\n                  static_cast\u003cstd::conditional\u003cstd::is_signed\u003cV\u003e::value,\n                                               int64_t,\n                                               uint64_t\u003e::type\u003e(iter-\u003esecond));",
      "revId": "6af88bcb0f8b0af0975c65a1c137012d7ead7917",
