      "writtenOn": "2017-06-09T21:06:12Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Using a static cast doesn\u0027t handle signed 32-bit values correctly.\ne.g. If the map contains 0x00000000ffffffff and V is int32_t, I want value to be -1.\nA static_cast\u003cint64_t\u003e(0x00000000ffffffff) produces 4294967295. There\u0027s no sign extension since we\u0027re casting from a uint64_t.\nI think there isn\u0027t any cast that does quite what I want.\nbit_cast is the closest but only works on same-size types.\n\nI\u0027ve pulled the bulk of the code out into VariableSizeBitCast as well as added some comments and broke up the big-endian memcpy to try and make it a little less opaque.\n\nWDYT?",
      "parentUuid": "34a6a09a_178f6e1c",
      "revId": "6af88bcb0f8b0af0975c65a1c137012d7ead7917",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
