      "writtenOn": "2017-06-09T21:10:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e Using a static cast doesn\u0027t handle signed 32-bit values correctly.\n\u003e e.g. If the map contains 0x00000000ffffffff and V is int32_t, I want value to be -1.\n\nAh, I see…in order for this to work, you’d have to sign-extend values when you put them into the map too. Then if you were looking at a 32-bit process, the map could never have 0x00000000ffffffff as a value, it’d have been stored as 0xffffffffffffffff.",
      "parentUuid": "b20308dc_43833420",
      "revId": "6af88bcb0f8b0af0975c65a1c137012d7ead7917",
